         <h3>Language Specific Feature Highlights</h3>
         <strong>Features: </strong>
     <ul>
     <li>Template set for each language</li>
     <li>System text for each language</li>
     <li>Language specific labels for all question types</li>
     <li>Language specific category names</li>
     <li>Language specific listing durations</li>
     <li>Language specific dropdown choices</li>
     <li>Can filter out listings not in current language browsed</li>
     <li>Can allow client to choose the language they browse site in</li>
     <li>Admin tool currently English only</li>
     </ul>
         </div>
       </div>
     </div>
   </div>

<!--ADD ON HIGHLIGHTS - END HERE-->

   <div style="padding: 4px 4px 4px 15px; text-align: left; margin-right: 20px;">
<p>
All client side <b>text and design can be managed by language</b>.  You have the ability to translate everything you see on the client side to the language you choose.  All field and questions labels can be translated.  All dropdown choices attached to those questions can be language specific.  Auction and classified ad duration choices appear by language.  Category names can be language specific.
</p>
<p>
Set <b>template sets per language</b>.  Each language you use within the software can have its own specific template set to allow you to design per language.  Sometimes a specific language has different needs within the html design like right to left languages like Arabic, Hebrew and others.  You can make html design specific changes to make sure these languages appear in right to left as needed. 
</p>
<p>
If your site supports more than one language you can <b>allow your clients to choose the language</b>they wish to view the site itself in within a system provided language choice page or create your own "flag links" that allow your clients to choose a language by clicking a flag or link.
</p>
<p>
You can filter listings within the caegory browsing and search features of the software so that<b>if a client is browsing the site in French they will only see French listings</b>.  The choice is yours for your site and one simple switch in the admin tool turns this feature on and off.
</p>
<p>
The software does not "auto translate" client inserted text to save you the embarrassment of causing disputes between clients on your site.  Auto translaters miss many nuances of languages and simply go off on tangents with listing detail syntax/semantics issues that can cause critical problems and disputes between buyers and sellers on your site.  If a seller inserts a listing in a specific language they are usually only able to answer questions about that listing in that one language.  
</p>
